{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1734,"text":"Guys, we have an issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4294,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":5416,"text":"Growth is fading away,\nand it's a big deal."},{"time":9136,"text":"Our global economy stops growing."},{"time":12018,"text":"And it's not new."},{"time":13441,"text":"Growth has actually declined\nfor the last 50 years."},{"time":17213,"text":"If we continue like this, we need to learn"},{"time":19777,"text":"how to live in a world\nwith no growth in the next decade."},{"time":24249,"text":"This is scary because\nwhen the economy doesn't grow,"},{"time":27750,"text":"our children don't get better lives."},{"time":30535,"text":"What's even scarier is that\nwhen the pie does not grow,"},{"time":33972,"text":"each of us get a smaller piece."},{"time":35552,"text":"We're then ready to fight\nfor a bigger one."},{"time":38070,"text":"This creates tensions\nand serious conflicts."},{"time":41585,"text":"Growth matters a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45350,"text":"If we look at the history of growth,"},{"time":47662,"text":"times of big growth\nhave always been fueled"},{"time":50198,"text":"by big manufacturing revolutions."},{"time":52818,"text":"It happened three times,\nevery 50-60 years."},{"time":56419,"text":"The steam engine\nin the middle of the 19th century,"},{"time":60467,"text":"the mass-production model\nin the beginning of the 20th century --"},{"time":64252,"text":"thanks, Mr. Ford."},{"time":66384,"text":"And the first automation\nwave in the 1970s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70157,"text":"Why did these manufacturing revolutions"},{"time":72377,"text":"create huge growth in our economies?"},{"time":75677,"text":"Because they have injected\nhuge productivity improvement."},{"time":79591,"text":"It's rather simple:"},{"time":81080,"text":"in order to grow,\nyou need to be producing more,"},{"time":84339,"text":"putting more into our economy."},{"time":87241,"text":"This means either more labor\nor more capital or more productivity."},{"time":92877,"text":"Each time, productivity\nhas been the growth lever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97744,"text":"I'm here today to tell you"},{"time":100511,"text":"that we are on the verge\nof another huge change,"},{"time":104245,"text":"and that this change, surprisingly enough,"},{"time":107731,"text":"is going to come\nfrom manufacturing, again."},{"time":111394,"text":"It will get us out of our growth slump"},{"time":114526,"text":"and it will change radically\nthe way globalization has been shaped"},{"time":118394,"text":"over the last decade."},{"time":119935,"text":"I'm here to tell you about the amazing\nfourth manufacturing revolution"},{"time":125230,"text":"that is currently underway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127213,"text":"It's not as if we've done nothing\nwith manufacturing"},{"time":129698,"text":"since the last revolution."},{"time":131011,"text":"Actually, we've made\nsome pretty lame attempts"},{"time":133450,"text":"to try to revitalize it."},{"time":135075,"text":"But none of them\nhave been the big overhaul"},{"time":138076,"text":"we really need to get us growing again."},{"time":140384,"text":"For example, we've tried\nto relocate our factories offshore"},{"time":145002,"text":"in order to reduce cost\nand take advantage of cheap labor."},{"time":149048,"text":"Not only did this not\ninspire productivity,"},{"time":152655,"text":"but it only saved money\nfor a short period of time,"},{"time":155151,"text":"because cheap labor\ndidn't stay cheap for long."},{"time":158455,"text":"Then, we've tried to make\nour factories larger"},{"time":162401,"text":"and we specialized them by product."},{"time":165318,"text":"The idea was that we can\nmake a lot of one product"},{"time":168655,"text":"and stockpile it to be sold with demand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172022,"text":"This did help productivity for a while."},{"time":174625,"text":"But it introduced a lot of rigidities\nin our supply chain."},{"time":179432,"text":"Let's take fashion retail."},{"time":181232,"text":"Traditional clothing companies"},{"time":183374,"text":"have built offshore,\nglobal, rigid supply chains."},{"time":188787,"text":"When fast-fashion competitors like Zara"},{"time":191562,"text":"started replenishing their stocks faster"},{"time":194097,"text":"from two collections a year\nto one collection a month,"},{"time":197800,"text":"none of them have been able\nto keep up with the pace."},{"time":200368,"text":"Most of them are\nin great difficulties today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204008,"text":"Yet, with all of their shortcomings,"},{"time":207236,"text":"those are the factories we know today."},{"time":209539,"text":"When you open the doors,"},{"time":211181,"text":"they look the same\nas they did 50 years ago."},{"time":214396,"text":"We've just changed the location,\nthe size, the way they operate."},{"time":220273,"text":"Can you name anything else\nthat looks the same"},{"time":222641,"text":"as it did 50 years ago?"},{"time":224220,"text":"It's crazy."},{"time":225836,"text":"We've made all the tweaks\nto the model that we could,"},{"time":228892,"text":"and now we hit its limits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233032,"text":"After all of our attempts to fix\nthe manufacturing model failed,"},{"time":237893,"text":"we thought growth could come\nfrom elsewhere."},{"time":240722,"text":"We turned to the tech sector --"},{"time":242786,"text":"there's been quite a lot\nof innovations there."},{"time":245178,"text":"Just to name one: the Internet."},{"time":247906,"text":"We hoped it could produce growth."},{"time":249735,"text":"And indeed, it changed our lives."},{"time":252251,"text":"It made big waves in the media,\nthe service, the entertainment spaces."},{"time":257081,"text":"But it hasn't done much for productivity."},{"time":260011,"text":"Actually, what's surprising\nis that productivity is on the decline"},{"time":264331,"text":"despite all of those innovation efforts."},{"time":267523,"text":"Imagine that -- sitting at work,\nscrolling through Facebook,"},{"time":271305,"text":"watching videos on YouTube\nhas made us less productive."},{"time":275133,"text":"Weird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276308,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":277916,"text":"This is why we are not growing."},{"time":280580,"text":"We failed at reinventing\nthe manufacturing space,"},{"time":283880,"text":"and large technological innovations\nhave played away from it."},{"time":289184,"text":"But what if we could combine those forces?"},{"time":291927,"text":"What if the existing manufacturing\nand large technological innovation"},{"time":296819,"text":"came together to create\nthe next big manufacturing reinvention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301406,"text":"Bingo!"},{"time":302688,"text":"This is the fourth\nmanufacturing revolution,"},{"time":305195,"text":"and it's happening right now."},{"time":307355,"text":"Major technologies are entering\nthe manufacturing space,"},{"time":310645,"text":"big time."},{"time":312316,"text":"They will boost industrial productivity\nby more than a third."},{"time":316217,"text":"This is massive, and it will do\na lot in creating growth."},{"time":321286,"text":"Let me tell you about some of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324091,"text":"Have you already met advanced\nmanufacturing robots?"},{"time":327583,"text":"They are the size of humans,"},{"time":329702,"text":"they actually collaborate with them,"},{"time":331747,"text":"and they can be programmed"},{"time":333350,"text":"in order to perform\ncomplex, non-repetitive tasks."},{"time":337628,"text":"Today in our factories, only\n8 percent of the tasks are automated."},{"time":342590,"text":"The less complex,\nthe more repetitive ones."},{"time":346551,"text":"It will be 25 percent in 10 years."},{"time":349452,"text":"It means that by 2025,"},{"time":352289,"text":"advanced robots will complement workers"},{"time":354877,"text":"to be, together,\n20 percent more productive,"},{"time":357744,"text":"to manufacture 20 percent more outputs,"},{"time":359769,"text":"to achieve 20 percent additional growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363118,"text":"This isn't some fancy, futuristic idea."},{"time":366425,"text":"These robots are working for us right now."},{"time":369993,"text":"Last year in the US, they helped\nAmazon prepare and ship all the products"},{"time":375563,"text":"required for Cyber Monday,"},{"time":377681,"text":"the annual peak of online retail."},{"time":380401,"text":"Last year in the US,"},{"time":382049,"text":"it was the biggest online shopping day\nof the year and of history."},{"time":388626,"text":"Consumers spent 3 billion dollars\non electronics that day."},{"time":392276,"text":"That's real economic growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395502,"text":"Then there's additive\nmanufacturing, 3D printing."},{"time":399574,"text":"3D printing has already improved\nplastic manufacturing"},{"time":403606,"text":"and it's now making its way through metal."},{"time":406614,"text":"Those are not small industries."},{"time":408875,"text":"Plastic and metals represent 25 percent"},{"time":411915,"text":"of global manufacturing production."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414717,"text":"Let's take a real example."},{"time":417005,"text":"In the aerospace industry,"},{"time":419967,"text":"fuel nozzles are some of the most\ncomplex parts to manufacture,"},{"time":424484,"text":"for one reason:"},{"time":425806,"text":"they are made up of 20 different parts"},{"time":429019,"text":"that need to be separately produced"},{"time":431854,"text":"and then painstakingly assembled."},{"time":435301,"text":"Aerospace companies\nare now using 3D printing,"},{"time":438451,"text":"which allows them to turn\nthose 20 different parts"},{"time":441539,"text":"into just one."},{"time":443368,"text":"The results?"},{"time":444909,"text":"40 percent more productivity,"},{"time":447269,"text":"40 percent more output produced,\n40 percent more growth"},{"time":450560,"text":"for this specific industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453283,"text":"But actually, the most exciting part\nof this new manufacturing revolution"},{"time":459457,"text":"goes much beyond productivity."},{"time":462692,"text":"It's about producing better,\nsmarter products."},{"time":466287,"text":"It's about scale customization."},{"time":469099,"text":"Imagine a world where you can buy\nthe exact products you want"},{"time":473858,"text":"with the functionalities you need,"},{"time":476092,"text":"with the design you want,"},{"time":478064,"text":"with the same cost and lead time"},{"time":479674,"text":"as a product that's been mass produced,"},{"time":481580,"text":"like your car, or your clothes\nor your cell phone."},{"time":485113,"text":"The new manufacturing revolution\nmakes it possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488577,"text":"Advanced robots can be programmed"},{"time":491422,"text":"in order to perform\nany product configuration"},{"time":494565,"text":"without any setup time or ramp up."},{"time":497791,"text":"3D printers instantaneously produce\nany customized design."},{"time":503675,"text":"We are now able to produce\na batch of one product, your product,"},{"time":509368,"text":"at the same cost and lead time\nas a batch of many."},{"time":513629,"text":"Those are only a few examples\nof the manufacturing revolution at play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518468,"text":"Not only will manufacturing\nbecome more productive,"},{"time":522579,"text":"it will also become more flexible,"},{"time":525538,"text":"and those were exactly the elements\nof growth that we are missing."},{"time":531106,"text":"But actually, there are even\nsome bigger implications"},{"time":534748,"text":"for all of us when manufacturing\nwill find its way back into the limelight."},{"time":540441,"text":"It will create a huge macroeconomic shift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544683,"text":"First, our factories will be relocated\ninto our home markets."},{"time":549877,"text":"In the world of scale customization,"},{"time":552144,"text":"consumer proximity is the new norm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555722,"text":"Then, our factories\nwill be smaller, agile."},{"time":559918,"text":"Scale does not matter anymore,\nflexibility does."},{"time":563802,"text":"They will be operating on a multi-product,\nmade-to-order basis."},{"time":567859,"text":"The change will be drastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570590,"text":"Globalization will enter a new era."},{"time":575145,"text":"The East-to-West trade flows"},{"time":578084,"text":"will be replaced by regional trade flows."},{"time":580789,"text":"East for East, West for West."},{"time":583687,"text":"When you think about that,"},{"time":585884,"text":"the old model was pretty much insane."},{"time":589065,"text":"Piling up stocks, making products\ntravel the whole world"},{"time":592840,"text":"before they reach their end consumers."},{"time":594743,"text":"The new model, producing\njust next to the consumer market,"},{"time":599007,"text":"will be much cleaner,\nmuch better for our environment."},{"time":604678,"text":"In mature economies,\nmanufacturing will be back home,"},{"time":608487,"text":"creating more employment,"},{"time":610587,"text":"more productivity and more growth."},{"time":613930,"text":"Good news, isn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616541,"text":"But here's the thing with growth --"},{"time":618370,"text":"it does not come automatically."},{"time":620328,"text":"Mature economies will have to seize it."},{"time":623196,"text":"We'll have to massively\nre-train our workforce."},{"time":626547,"text":"In most countries,\nlike in my country, France,"},{"time":629231,"text":"we've told our children\nthat manufacturing had no future."},{"time":632357,"text":"That it was something happening far away."},{"time":634358,"text":"We need to reverse that"},{"time":636180,"text":"and teach manufacturing again\nat university."},{"time":639203,"text":"Only the countries\nthat will boldly transform"},{"time":642712,"text":"will be able to seize this growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646640,"text":"It's also a chance\nfor developing economies."},{"time":650461,"text":"Of course China\nand other emerging economies"},{"time":654118,"text":"won't be the factory of the world anymore."},{"time":657545,"text":"Actually, it was not a sustainable\nmodel in the long term,"},{"time":662187,"text":"as those countries are becoming richer."},{"time":665779,"text":"Last year, it was already\nas expensive to produce in Brazil"},{"time":670827,"text":"as to produce in France."},{"time":674184,"text":"By 2018, manufacturing costs in China\nwill be on par with the US."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681350,"text":"The new manufacturing revolution"},{"time":683625,"text":"will accelerate the transition\nof those emerging economies"},{"time":688429,"text":"towards a model driven\nby domestic consumption."},{"time":691675,"text":"And this is good,"},{"time":692876,"text":"because this is where growth\nwill be created."},{"time":695915,"text":"In the next five years,"},{"time":697543,"text":"the next billion consumers in China\nwill inject more growth in our economies"},{"time":702871,"text":"than the top five\nEuropean markets together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707944,"text":"This fourth manufacturing revolution\nis a chance for all of us."},{"time":713046,"text":"If we play it right,"},{"time":715024,"text":"we'll see sustainable growth\nin all of our economies."},{"time":718969,"text":"This means more wealth\ndistributed to all of us"},{"time":722658,"text":"and a better future for our children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725189,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726374,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}